 the Masses? Justification for the Public Support of the Arts in Developing Countries \u2013 Two Arts Festivals in South Africa|journal=Journal of Cultural Economics|volume=29|issue=2|year=2005|pages=107\u2013125|issn=0885-2545|doi=10.1007/s10824-005-5064-5}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Snowball|first1=J.D.|title=Valuing the Arts|last2=Antrobus|first2=G.G.|journal=South African Journal of Economics|volume=70|issue=8|year=2005|pages=1297\u20131319|issn=0038-2280|doi=10.1111/j.1813-6982.2002.tb00067.x}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Snowball|first1=J.D.|title=Interpreting Economic Impact Study Results: Spending Patterns, Visitor Numbers and Festival Aims|journal=South African Journal of Economics|volume=72|issue=5|year=2005|pages=1076\u20131084|issn=0038-2280|doi=10.1111/j.1813-6982.2004.tb00146.x}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Bain|first1=Keith|title=Make Believe: Standard Bank National Arts Festival Grahamstown, 2\u201312 July 1998|journal=South African Theatre Journal|volume=12|issue=1\u20132|year=1998|pages=137\u2013164|issn=1013-7548|doi=10.1080/10137548.1998.9687669}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=van der Vyver|first1=Abraham G.|last2=du Plooy-Cilliers|first2=Franz\u00e9l|title=The social dynamics of arts festivals: A comparative analysis of the KKNK and the Grahamstown National Arts Festival|journal=South African Theatre Journal|volume=20|issue=1|year=2006|pages=192\u2013203|issn=1013-7548|doi=10.1080/10137548.2006.9687832}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Kitshoff|first1=Herman|title=Grahamstown National Arts Festival\u2014Grahamstown, 1\u201310 July 2004|journal=South African Theatre Journal|volume=18|issue=1|year=2004|pages=246\u2013249|issn=1013-7548|doi=10.1080/10137548.2004.9687791}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Lewis|first1=Megan|title=Standard Bank National Arts Festival, Grahamstown, South Africa, 3\u201313 July 1997 (review)|journal=Theatre Journal|volume=50|issue=1|year=1998|pages=105\u2013107|issn=1086-332X|doi=10.1353/tj.1998.0018}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Neethling|first1=Miemie|t